gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: S88 T3 — Trust device: direct app entry without biometry or password
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV, MOBILE_TAURI]
sprint: S88

context: |
  Alternative to Face ID for users who prefer convenience over device-level lock.
  When local_trust_device is true AND local_use_biometry is false:
  - Cold start: restore session automatically (no Face ID, no login form).
  - Skip useSessionBiometryLock gates entirely.
  - If JWT valid → hydrate and navigate to objects.
  - If JWT expired → silent relogin from stored credentials (no biometry
    prompt on vault read — use non-biometric durable storage for trust mode only).

steps:
  1. Add local_trust_device: boolean to useLocalSettings (default false).
  2. Mutual exclusion: enabling trust device forces local_use_biometry false;
     enabling biometry forces local_trust_device false.
  3. When trust device on: persist JWT in durable storage (tauri store or
     localStorage), not sessionStorage-only; release token gate on startup.
  4. useSessionBiometryLock early-return when trust device active.
  5. On app init (App.tsx or useAuthFlow): if trust + valid token → objects;
     if trust + expired token + creds → reloginWithBiometricCredentials without
     loadBiometricCredentials Face ID round-trip (trust-scoped credential read).
  6. Explicit logout clears trust session storage and requires password.

out:
  - src/hooks/useLocalSettings.ts
  - src/lib/api-auth.ts
  - src/features/security/hooks/useSessionBiometryLock.ts
  - src/features/security/lib/biometric-credentials.ts
  - src/shell/hooks/useAuthFlow.ts
  - src/store/useAuthStore.ts

done:
  - Trust device ON, biometry OFF → kill app → reopen → main screen, no prompts.
  - Trust device OFF, biometry ON → existing Face ID flow unchanged.
  - Trust + explicit logout → login with password required.
  - No trust mode without user opt-in (T4 warning gate).
